    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NIA1 integrity algorithm initialization causing protocol state violations\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1_init()` function was incorrectly implemented using `nas_stream_cipher_t` as the persistent security context structure. This caused memory layout mismatches during integrity computations, leading to protocol state machine violations that affected downstream 3GPP specification compliance.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_pdcp/nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1.c`: Refactored initialization to allocate only the 16-byte integrity key, matching the EIA1 implementation pattern\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_pdcp/nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1.c`: Modified integrity computation to use temporary `nas_stream_cipher_t` structures per call\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_pdcp/nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1.c`: Simplified cleanup to match EIA1 implementation\n\n### Reproduction\nDevices using NIA1 integrity protection may experience:\n- PDCP integrity verification failures\n- RRC connection establishment failures  \n- Protocol state machine transitions that violate 3GPP TS 38.323 specifications\n- Intermittent connection drops during security activation\n\nThe issue manifests when NIA1 is selected as the integrity algorithm during security mode command processing, causing incorrect MAC-I calculations that fail integrity checks at the receiving end.\n"
}